{
  "answer": "> **Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, Ghazal 102**\n\n> **Matla (opening couplet), original Urdu:**  \n> کب وہ سنتا ہے کہانی میری  \n> اور پھر وہ بھی زبانی میری[^1]\n\n> **Transliteration:**  \n> Kab woh sunta hai kahani meri  \n> Aur phir woh bhi zabani meri[^2]\n\n> **English translation:**  \n> He never hears the story I maintain is mine;  \n> And even spoken, the attempt in vain is mine.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/102-kab-woh-sunta-hai-kahani-meri/original/#p-f1ea96).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [chapter](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/102-kab-woh-sunta-hai-kahani-meri/transliteration/).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/102-kab-woh-sunta-hai-kahani-meri/translation/#p-a9dedb).",
